{{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | caption = | name = Ma Ruifang | native_name = 马瑞芳 / ﻣَﺎ ژُﻮِ ﻓْﺎ | native_name_lang = zh-hans | birth_name = | other_names = | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1942}} | birth_place = [[Qingzhou]], [[Shandong]], [[Republic of China (1912–1949)|Republic of China]] | death_date = <!--卒年在前生年在后{{death date and age|}} --> | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = [[Shandong]] | education = | alma_mater = [[Shandong University]] | occupation = author, [[scholar]], and [[professor]] | years_active = 1978 - present | organization = | agent = | known_for = literature of Pu Songling in the [[CCTV-10]] program ''[[Lecture Room]]'' | notable_works = | television = The [[CCTV-10]] program ''[[Lecture Room]]'' | party = | movement = | spouse = Niu Yunqing ({{lang|zh-hans|牛运清}}) | partner = | children = | parents = Ma Chuzhen ({{lang|zh-hans|马楚珍}}) | relatives = grandpa Ma Defu ({{lang|zh-hans|马德甫}}) | awards = <!-- {{Awards|award= |year= |title= }} --> | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = }} {{Chinese name|[[Ma (surname)|Ma]]}} '''Ma Ruifang'''({{zh|s=马瑞芳|t=馬瑞芳|p=Mǎ Ruìfāng}}， [[Xiao'erjing]]: {{lang|zh-Arab|ﻣَﺎ ژُﻮِ ﻓْﺎ }}; born 1942) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] author, [[scholar]] and [[professor]] at the School of Literature, [[Shandong University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.qlwb.com.cn/display.asp?id=240589 |script-title=zh:马瑞芳推出"儒林新外传" |date=2007 |work=qlwb.com.cn |publisher= |language=Chinese }}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=" cscst" >{{cite web |url= http://www.cctv.com/program/bjjt/20050113/101147.shtml|script-title=zh:《人鬼情未了》 马瑞芳 |date= 2005|work=CCTV|publisher=|language =Chinese}}</ref>
==Biography== Ma was born in 1942 in [[Qingzhou]], [[Shandong Province]]. Her grandfather Ma Defu ({{lang|zh-hans|马德甫}}) and father Ma Chuzhen ({{lang|zh-hans|马楚珍}}) were doctors. She belonged to the [[Hui people|Hui]] ethnic group. Her mother was educated. Ma read books in Yidu County Library ({{lang|zh-hans|益都县图书馆}}) when she studied at [[primary school]]. She was accepted into Shandong University and graduated in 1965. In 1966,[[Mao Zedong]] launched the [[Cultural revolution]] and she was persecuted. In 1980, Ma started to study the literature of [[Pu Songling]].<ref name="wyis " >{{cite web |url=http://news.163.com/07/0907/15/3NQ2K8RV000120GU.html |title=主讲人马瑞芳:学者最重要品质是正直 |date= 2007|work=163.com|publisher=|language =Chinese}}</ref>
Ma became popular in [[China]] for her lectures on literature of Pu Songling in the [[CCTV-10]] program ''[[Lecture Room]]'' in 2005.
